# CDS-Responsive-Assist - Cursor AI Rules

## System Context

You are working with the CDS (Component Design System) documentation repository. This contains comprehensive documentation for 70+ Material-UI v6.1.0 components with full CDS token integration, WCAG 2.1 Level AA accessibility compliance, and 400+ production-ready code examples.

## Component Documentation Available

All components are documented in files named: `DESIGN-SYSTEM-DOCUMENTATION-[COMPONENT].md`

Categories (70+ components):
- Foundation & Layout (7): Box, Container, Grid, Stack, Paper, Divider, Link
- Navigation (9): AppBar, BottomNavigation, Drawer, Menu, Tabs, Pagination, SpeedDial, TreeView, Stepper
- Buttons (6): Button, IconButton, FAB, ButtonGroup, ToggleButton, LoadingButton
- Form Inputs (12): TextField, Checkbox, Radio, Switch, Select, Slider, Rating, FormLabel, TransferList, DatePicker, TimePicker
- Data Display (13): Avatar, Badge, List, Table, ImageList, Accordion, Card, Chip, Typography, Tooltip
- Feedback (9): Alert, Progress, Skeleton, Backdrop, LinearProgress, CircularProgress, Snackbar, Dialog
- Utility (6): Popover, Collapse, ClickAwayListener, Modal, Transition, Portal
- Advanced (2): FileUpload, Custom implementations

## Design Token System (8 Categories)

### 1. Colors
```typescript
palette.primary.main, palette.secondary.main
palette.error, palette.success, palette.warning, palette.info
palette.text.primary, palette.text.secondary, palette.text.disabled
palette.background.default, palette.background.paper
palette.action.active, palette.action.hover, palette.action.disabled
```

### 2. Spacing (4px grid)
```typescript
spacing(1) = 4px, spacing(2) = 8px, spacing(3) = 12px, spacing(4) = 16px
spacing(6) = 24px, spacing(8) = 32px
```

### 3. Typography
```typescript
h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6, body1, body2, button, caption, overline
```

### 4. Sizing
```typescript
Touch targets: 48px minimum
Icon sizes: 20px (small), 24px (medium), 32px (large)
Button heights: 32px (small), 40px (medium), 48px (large)
```

### 5. Elevation
```typescript
0 = flat, 1 = subtle, 4 = app bar, 8 = floating, 16 = drawer, 24 = max
```

### 6. Z-Index
```typescript
1000 = elevated, 1100 = app bar, 1200 = drawer, 1300 = modal, 1400 = dialog, 1500 = tooltip
```

### 7. Border Radius
```typescript
2px = extra small, 4px = default, 8px = medium, 12px = large, 50% = circular
```

### 8. Transitions
```typescript
duration: 150ms (shortest), 200ms (shorter), 300ms (standard), 375ms (complex)
easing: easeInOut, easeOut, easeIn, sharp
```

## Code Generation Rules

### Always Do
1. Import from @mui/material: `import Button from '@mui/material/Button'`
2. Use CDS design tokens (never hard-code colors, spacing, etc.)
3. Include ARIA attributes for accessibility
4. Provide keyboard navigation support
5. Use semantic HTML elements
6. Follow mobile-first responsive design (xs, sm, md, lg, xl)
7. Ensure 48px minimum touch targets
8. Maintain 4.5:1 color contrast for text
9. Add helper text for form inputs
10. Include loading and error states

### Never Do
1. Hard-code colors: Use `color="primary"` or `sx={{ color: 'primary.main' }}`
2. Hard-code spacing: Use `sx={{ p: 2 }}` instead of `padding: '8px'`
3. Skip accessibility attributes
4. Ignore responsive breakpoints
5. Use non-semantic HTML (div buttons, etc.)
6. Create inaccessible touch targets (<48px)
7. Skip error handling in forms
8. Forget loading states for async actions

## WCAG 2.1 Level AA Requirements

All generated code must meet:
- Keyboard navigation (Tab, Enter, Space, Arrow keys)
- ARIA attributes (aria-label, aria-describedby, role)
- Color contrast: 4.5:1 for text, 3:1 for non-text
- Touch targets: 48px × 48px minimum
- Visible focus indicators
- Screen reader support
- Clear error messages

## Responsive Breakpoints

```typescript
xs: 0px      // Mobile portrait
sm: 600px    // Mobile landscape / Tablet portrait
md: 900px    // Tablet landscape
lg: 1200px   // Desktop
xl: 1536px   // Large desktop
```

## Common Patterns

### Navigation
```tsx
// Desktop: AppBar + Drawer
<AppBar position="fixed" elevation={4}>
  <Toolbar>...</Toolbar>
</AppBar>
<Drawer variant="permanent" elevation={16}>
  <List>...</List>
</Drawer>

// Mobile: BottomNavigation
<BottomNavigation elevation={8} showLabels>
  <BottomNavigationAction label="Home" icon={<HomeIcon />} />
</BottomNavigation>
```

### Forms
```tsx
<Container maxWidth="sm">
  <Stack spacing={3} component="form">
    <TextField label="Email" type="email" required fullWidth />
    <LoadingButton variant="contained" loading={isLoading}>
      Submit
    </LoadingButton>
  </Stack>
</Container>
```

### Data Display
```tsx
<Grid container spacing={3}>
  <Grid item xs={12} sm={6} md={4}>
    <Card elevation={1}>
      <CardHeader avatar={<Avatar>A</Avatar>} title="Title" />
      <CardContent>...</CardContent>
    </Card>
  </Grid>
</Grid>
```

### Loading States
```tsx
{loading ? (
  <Stack spacing={1}>
    <Skeleton variant="text" width="60%" />
    <Skeleton variant="rectangular" height={118} />
  </Stack>
) : (
  <Content />
)}
```

